var book = {
	"name": "Judges",
	"numChapters": 21,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>After the death of Joshua, the people of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6511A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6511A\"></sup>inquired of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6511B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6511B\"></sup>“Who shall go up first for us against the Canaanites, to fight against them?”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “Judah shall go up; behold, I have given the land into his hand.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And Judah said to Simeon his brother, “Come up with me into the territory allotted to me, that we may fight against the Canaanites. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6513C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6513C\"></sup>And I likewise will go with you into the territory allotted to you.” So Simeon went with him.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then Judah went up and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave the Canaanites and the Perizzites into their hand, and they defeated 10,000 of them at Bezek.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They found Adoni-bezek at Bezek and fought against him and defeated the Canaanites and the Perizzites.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Adoni-bezek fled, but they pursued him and caught him and cut off his thumbs and his big toes.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And Adoni-bezek said, “Seventy kings with their thumbs and their big toes cut off <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6517D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6517D\"></sup>used to pick up scraps under my table. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6517E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6517E\"></sup>As I have done, so God has repaid me.” And they brought him to Jerusalem, and he died there.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6518F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6518F\"></sup>And the men of Judah fought against Jerusalem and captured it and struck it with the edge of the sword and set the city on fire.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And afterward the men of Judah went down to fight against the Canaanites who lived in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6519G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6519G\"></sup>the hill country, in the Negeb, and in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6519H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6519H\"></sup>the lowland.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6520I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6520I\"></sup>And Judah went against the Canaanites who lived in Hebron <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6520J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6520J\"></sup>(now the name of Hebron was formerly Kiriath-arba), and they defeated <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6520K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6520K\"></sup>Sheshai and Ahiman and Talmai.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>From there they went against the inhabitants of Debir. The name of Debir was formerly Kiriath-sepher.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And Caleb said, “He who attacks Kiriath-sepher and captures it, I will give him Achsah my daughter for a wife.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And Othniel the son of Kenaz, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6523L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6523L\"></sup>Caleb's younger brother, captured it. And he gave him Achsah his daughter for a wife.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When she came to him, she urged him to ask her father for a field. And she dismounted from her donkey, and Caleb said to her, “What do you want?”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>She said to him, “Give me a blessing. Since you have set me in the land of the Negeb, give me also springs of water.” And Caleb gave her the upper springs and the lower springs.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And the descendants of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6526M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6526M\"></sup>Kenite, Moses' father-in-law, went up with the people of Judah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6526N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6526N\"></sup>from the city of palms into the wilderness of Judah, which lies in the Negeb near <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6526O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6526O\"></sup>Arad, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6526P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6526P\"></sup>and they went and settled with the people.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6527Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6527Q\"></sup>And Judah went with Simeon his brother, and they defeated the Canaanites who inhabited Zephath and devoted it to destruction. So the name of the city was called <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6527R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6527R\"></sup>Hormah.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Judah also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6528S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6528S\"></sup>captured Gaza with its territory, and Ashkelon with its territory, and Ekron with its territory.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6529T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6529T\"></sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was with Judah, and he took possession of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6529U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6529U\"></sup>hill country, but he could not drive out the inhabitants of the plain because they had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6529V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6529V\"></sup>chariots of iron.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6530W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6530W\"></sup>And Hebron was given to Caleb, as Moses had said. And he drove out from it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6530X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6530X\"></sup>the three sons of Anak.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But the people of Benjamin did not drive out the Jebusites who lived in Jerusalem, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6531Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6531Y\"></sup>so the Jebusites have lived with the people of Benjamin in Jerusalem to this day.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The house of Joseph also went up against Bethel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6532Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6532Z\"></sup>and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was with them.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And the house of Joseph scouted out Bethel. (<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6533AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6533AA\"></sup>Now the name of the city was formerly Luz.)",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And the spies saw a man coming out of the city, and they said to him, “Please show us the way into the city, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6534AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6534AB\"></sup>and we will deal kindly with you.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And he showed them the way into the city. And they struck the city with the edge of the sword, but they let the man and all his family go.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And the man went to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6536AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6536AC\"></sup>the land of the Hittites and built a city and called its name Luz. That is its name to this day.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6537AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6537AD\"></sup>Manasseh did not drive out the inhabitants of Beth-shean and its villages, or Taanach and its villages, or the inhabitants of Dor and its villages, or the inhabitants of Ibleam and its villages, or the inhabitants of Megiddo and its villages, for the Canaanites persisted in dwelling in that land.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>When Israel grew strong, they put the Canaanites to forced labor, but did not drive them out completely.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6539AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6539AE\"></sup>And Ephraim did not drive out the Canaanites who lived in Gezer, so the Canaanites lived in Gezer among them.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Zebulun did not drive out the inhabitants of Kitron, or the inhabitants of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6540AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6540AF\"></sup>Nahalol, so the Canaanites lived among them, but became subject to forced labor.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6541AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6541AG\"></sup>Asher did not drive out the inhabitants of Acco, or the inhabitants of Sidon or of Ahlab or of Achzib or of Helbah or of Aphik or of Rehob,",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>so the Asherites lived among the Canaanites, the inhabitants of the land, for they did not drive them out.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Naphtali did not drive out the inhabitants of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6543AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6543AH\"></sup>Beth-shemesh, or the inhabitants of Beth-anath, so they lived among the Canaanites, the inhabitants of the land. Nevertheless, the inhabitants of Beth-shemesh and of Beth-anath became subject to forced labor for them.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6544AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6544AI\"></sup>The Amorites pressed the people of Dan back into the hill country, for they did not allow them to come down to the plain.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>The Amorites persisted in dwelling in Mount Heres, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6545AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6545AJ\"></sup>in Aijalon, and in Shaalbim, but the hand of the house of Joseph rested heavily on them, and they became subject to forced labor.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>And the border of the Amorites ran from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6546AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6546AK\"></sup>the ascent of Akrabbim, from Sela and upward."
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>Now the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> went up from Gilgal to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6547A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6547A\"></sup>Bochim. And he said, “I brought you up from Egypt and brought you into the land that I swore to give to your fathers. I said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6547B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6547B\"></sup>‘I will never break my covenant with you,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6548C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6548C\"></sup>and you shall make no covenant with the inhabitants of this land; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6548D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6548D\"></sup>you shall break down their altars.’ But you have not obeyed my voice. What is this you have done?",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So now I say, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6549E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6549E\"></sup>I will not drive them out before you, but they shall become <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6549F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6549F\"></sup>thorns in your sides, and their gods shall be a snare to you.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>As soon as the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke these words to all the people of Israel, the people lifted up their voices and wept.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And they called the name of that place Bochim. And they sacrificed there to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When Joshua dismissed the people, the people of Israel went each to his inheritance to take possession of the land.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6553G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6553G\"></sup>And the people served the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> all the days of Joshua, and all the days of the elders who outlived Joshua, who had seen all the great work that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had done for Israel.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And Joshua the son of Nun, the servant of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, died at the age of 110 years.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And they buried him within the boundaries of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6555H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6555H\"></sup>his inheritance in Timnath-heres, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6555I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6555I\"></sup>in the hill country of Ephraim, north of the mountain of Gaash.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And all that generation also were gathered to their fathers. And there arose another generation after them who did not know the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> or the work that he had done for Israel.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6557J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6557J\"></sup>And the people of Israel did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and served the Baals.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6558K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6558K\"></sup>And they abandoned the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their fathers, who had brought them out of the land of Egypt. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6558L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6558L\"></sup>They went after other gods, from among the gods of the peoples who were around them, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6558M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6558M\"></sup>bowed down to them. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6558N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6558N\"></sup>And they provoked the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to anger.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>They abandoned the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6559O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6559O\"></sup>and served the Baals and the Ashtaroth.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6560P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6560P\"></sup>So the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was kindled against Israel, and he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6560Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6560Q\"></sup>gave them over to plunderers, who plundered them. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6560R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6560R\"></sup>And he sold them into the hand of their surrounding enemies, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6560S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6560S\"></sup>so that they could no longer withstand their enemies.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Whenever they marched out, the hand of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was against them for harm, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had warned, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6561T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6561T\"></sup>and as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had sworn to them. And they were in terrible distress.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6562U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6562U\"></sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> raised up judges, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6562V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6562V\"></sup>who saved them out of the hand of those who plundered them.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Yet they did not listen to their judges, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6563W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6563W\"></sup>they whored after other gods and bowed down to them. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6563X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6563X\"></sup>They soon turned aside from the way in which their fathers had walked, who had obeyed the commandments of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and they did not do so.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Whenever the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> raised up judges for them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6564Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6564Y\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was with the judge, and he saved them from the hand of their enemies all the days of the judge. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6564Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6564Z\"></sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was moved to pity by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6564AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6564AA\"></sup>their groaning because of those who afflicted and oppressed them.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6565AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6565AB\"></sup>whenever the judge died, they turned back and were more corrupt than their fathers, going after other gods, serving them and bowing down to them. They did not drop any of their practices or their stubborn ways.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6566AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6566AC\"></sup>So the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was kindled against Israel, and he said, “Because this people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6566AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6566AD\"></sup>have transgressed my covenant that I commanded their fathers and have not obeyed my voice,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6567AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6567AE\"></sup>I will no longer drive out before them any of the nations that Joshua left when he died,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>in order <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6568AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6568AF\"></sup>to test Israel by them, whether they will take care to walk in the way of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> as their fathers did, or not.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> left those nations, not driving them out quickly, and he did not give them into the hand of Joshua."
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6570A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6570A\"></sup>Now these are the nations that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> left, to test Israel by them, that is, all in Israel who had not experienced all the wars in Canaan.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>It was only in order that the generations of the people of Israel might know war, to teach war to those who had not known it before.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>These are the nations: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6572B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6572B\"></sup>the five lords of the Philistines and all the Canaanites and the Sidonians and the Hivites who lived on Mount Lebanon, from Mount Baal-hermon as far as Lebo-hamath.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>They were for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6573C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6573C\"></sup>the testing of Israel, to know whether Israel would obey the commandments of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which he commanded their fathers by the hand of Moses.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So the people of Israel lived <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6574D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6574D\"></sup>among the Canaanites, the Hittites, the Amorites, the Perizzites, the Hivites, and the Jebusites.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6575E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6575E\"></sup>And their daughters they took to themselves for wives, and their own daughters they gave to their sons, and they served their gods.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6576F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6576F\"></sup>And the people of Israel did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. They forgot the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God and served the Baals and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6576G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6576G\"></sup>the Asheroth.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Therefore the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was kindled against Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6577H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6577H\"></sup>and he sold them into the hand of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6577I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6577I\"></sup>Cushan-rishathaim king of Mesopotamia. And the people of Israel served Cushan-rishathaim eight years.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But when the people of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6578J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6578J\"></sup>cried out to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> raised up a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6578K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6578K\"></sup>deliverer for the people of Israel, who saved them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6578L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6578L\"></sup>Othniel the son of Kenaz, Caleb's younger brother.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6579M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6579M\"></sup>The Spirit of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was upon him, and he judged Israel. He went out to war, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave Cushan-rishathaim king of Mesopotamia into his hand. And his hand prevailed over Cushan-rishathaim.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6580N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6580N\"></sup>So the land had rest forty years. Then Othniel the son of Kenaz died.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6581O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6581O\"></sup>And the people of Israel again did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> strengthened Eglon <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6581P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6581P\"></sup>the king of Moab against Israel, because they had done what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He gathered to himself the Ammonites and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6582Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6582Q\"></sup>Amalekites, and went and defeated Israel. And they took possession of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6582R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6582R\"></sup>the city of palms.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And the people of Israel served Eglon the king of Moab eighteen years.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then the people of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6584S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6584S\"></sup>cried out to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> raised up for them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6584T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6584T\"></sup>a deliverer, Ehud, the son of Gera, the Benjaminite, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6584U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6584U\"></sup>a left-handed man. The people of Israel sent tribute by him to Eglon the king of Moab.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And Ehud made for himself a sword with two edges, a cubit in length, and he bound it on his right thigh under his clothes.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And he presented the tribute to Eglon king of Moab. Now Eglon was a very fat man.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And when Ehud had finished presenting the tribute, he sent away the people who carried the tribute.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But he himself turned back <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6588V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6588V\"></sup>at the idols near Gilgal and said, “I have a secret message for you, O king.” And he commanded, “Silence.” And all his attendants went out from his presence.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And Ehud came to him as he was sitting alone in his <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6589W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6589W\"></sup>cool roof chamber. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6589X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6589X\"></sup>And Ehud said, “I have a message from God for you.” And he arose from his seat.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And Ehud reached with his left hand, took the sword from his right thigh, and thrust it into his belly.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And the hilt also went in after the blade, and the fat closed over the blade, for he did not pull the sword out of his belly; and the dung came out.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then Ehud went out into the porch and closed the doors of the roof chamber behind him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6592Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6592Y\"></sup>and locked them.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>When he had gone, the servants came, and when they saw that the doors of the roof chamber were locked, they thought, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6593Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6593Z\"></sup>“Surely he is relieving himself in the closet of the cool chamber.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And they waited till they were embarrassed. But when he still did not open the doors of the roof chamber, they took the key and opened them, and there lay their lord dead on the floor.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Ehud escaped while they delayed, and he passed beyond <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6595AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6595AA\"></sup>the idols and escaped to Seirah.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>When he arrived, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6596AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6596AB\"></sup>he sounded the trumpet in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6596AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6596AC\"></sup>the hill country of Ephraim. Then the people of Israel went down with him from the hill country, and he was their leader.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And he said to them, “Follow after me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6597AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6597AD\"></sup>for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given your enemies the Moabites into your hand.” So they went down after him and seized <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6597AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6597AE\"></sup>the fords of the Jordan against the Moabites and did not allow anyone to pass over.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And they killed at that time about 10,000 of the Moabites, all strong, able-bodied men; not a man escaped.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>So Moab was subdued that day under the hand of Israel. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6599AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6599AF\"></sup>And the land had rest for eighty years.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>After him was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6600AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6600AG\"></sup>Shamgar the son of Anath, who killed 600 of the Philistines <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6600AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6600AH\"></sup>with an oxgoad, and he also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6600AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6600AI\"></sup>saved Israel."
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6601A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6601A\"></sup>And the people of Israel again did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> after Ehud died.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6602B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6602B\"></sup>sold them into the hand of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6602C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6602C\"></sup>Jabin king of Canaan, who reigned in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6602D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6602D\"></sup>Hazor. The commander of his army was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6602E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6602E\"></sup>Sisera, who lived in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6602F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6602F\"></sup>Harosheth-hagoyim.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then the people of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6603G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6603G\"></sup>cried out to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for help, for he had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6603H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6603H\"></sup>900 chariots of iron and he oppressed the people of Israel cruelly for twenty years.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Now Deborah, a prophetess, the wife of Lappidoth, was judging Israel at that time.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>She used to sit under the palm of Deborah between Ramah and Bethel in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6605I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6605I\"></sup>the hill country of Ephraim, and the people of Israel came up to her for judgment.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>She sent and summoned <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6606J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6606J\"></sup>Barak the son of Abinoam from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6606K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6606K\"></sup>Kedesh-naphtali and said to him, “Has not the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, commanded you, ‘Go, gather your men at Mount <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6606L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6606L\"></sup>Tabor, taking 10,000 from the people of Naphtali and the people of Zebulun.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And I will draw out Sisera, the general of Jabin's army, to meet you by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6607M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6607M\"></sup>the river Kishon with his chariots and his troops, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6607N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6607N\"></sup>and I will give him into your hand’?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Barak said to her, “If you will go with me, I will go, but if you will not go with me, I will not go.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And she said, “I will surely go with you. Nevertheless, the road on which you are going will not lead to your glory, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6609O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6609O\"></sup>sell Sisera into the hand of a woman.” Then Deborah arose and went with Barak to Kedesh.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And Barak called out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6610P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6610P\"></sup>Zebulun and Naphtali to Kedesh. And 10,000 men went up at his heels, and Deborah went up with him.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now Heber <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6611Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6611Q\"></sup>the Kenite had separated from the Kenites, the descendants of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6611R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6611R\"></sup>Hobab the father-in-law of Moses, and had pitched his tent as far away as the oak in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6611S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6611S\"></sup>Zaanannim, which is near Kedesh.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>When Sisera was told that Barak the son of Abinoam had gone up to Mount Tabor,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Sisera called out all his chariots, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6613T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6613T\"></sup>900 chariots of iron, and all the men who were with him, from Harosheth-hagoyim to the river Kishon.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And Deborah said to Barak, “Up! For this is the day in which <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6614U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6614U\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given Sisera into your hand. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6614V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6614V\"></sup>Does not the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> go out before you?” So Barak went down from Mount Tabor with 10,000 men following him.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6615W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6615W\"></sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> routed Sisera and all his chariots and all his army before Barak by the edge of the sword. And Sisera got down from his chariot and fled away on foot.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And Barak pursued the chariots and the army to Harosheth-hagoyim, and all the army of Sisera fell by the edge of the sword; not a man was left.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But Sisera fled away on foot to the tent of Jael, the wife of Heber the Kenite, for there was peace between Jabin the king of Hazor and the house of Heber the Kenite.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And Jael came out to meet Sisera and said to him, “Turn aside, my lord; turn aside to me; do not be afraid.” So he turned aside to her into the tent, and she covered him with a rug.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And he said to her, “Please give me a little water to drink, for I am thirsty.” So she opened <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6619X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6619X\"></sup>a skin of milk and gave him a drink and covered him.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And he said to her, “Stand at the opening of the tent, and if any man comes and asks you, ‘Is anyone here?’ say, ‘No.’”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But Jael the wife of Heber took a tent peg, and took a hammer in her hand. Then she went softly to him and drove the peg into his temple until it went down into the ground while he was lying fast asleep from weariness. So he died.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And behold, as Barak was pursuing Sisera, Jael went out to meet him and said to him, “Come, and I will show you the man whom you are seeking.” So he went in to her tent, and there lay Sisera dead, with the tent peg in his temple.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6623Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6623Y\"></sup>So on that day God subdued Jabin the king of Canaan before the people of Israel.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And the hand of the people of Israel pressed harder and harder against Jabin the king of Canaan, until they destroyed Jabin king of Canaan."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6625A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6625A\"></sup>Then sang Deborah and Barak the son of Abinoam on that day:",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“That the leaders took the lead in Israel,that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6626B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6626B\"></sup>the people offered themselves willingly,bless the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“Hear, O kings; give ear, O princes;to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> I will sing;I will make melody to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“<span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6628C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6628C\"></sup>when you went out from Seir,when you marched from the region of Edom,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6628D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6628D\"></sup>the earth trembledand the heavens dropped,yes, the clouds dropped water.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The mountains <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6629E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6629E\"></sup>quaked before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6629F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6629F\"></sup>even Sinai before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“In the days of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6630G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6630G\"></sup>Shamgar, son of Anath,in the days of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6630H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6630H\"></sup>Jael, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6630I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6630I\"></sup>the highways were abandoned,and travelers kept to the byways.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The villagers ceased in Israel;they ceased to be until I arose;I, Deborah, arose as a mother in Israel.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6632J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6632J\"></sup>When new gods were chosen,then war was in the gates.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6632K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6632K\"></sup>Was shield or spear to be seenamong forty thousand in Israel?",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>My heart goes out to the commanders of Israelwho <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6633L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6633L\"></sup>offered themselves willingly among the people.Bless the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“Tell of it, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6634M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6634M\"></sup>you who ride on white donkeys,you who sit on rich carpetsand you who walk by the way.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>To the sound of musicians at the watering places,there they repeat the righteous triumphs of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,the righteous triumphs of his villagers in Israel.“Then down to the gates marched the people of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6636N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6636N\"></sup>“Awake, awake, Deborah!Awake, awake, break out in a song!Arise, Barak, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6636O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6636O\"></sup>lead away your captives,O son of Abinoam.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then down marched the remnant of the noble;the people of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> marched down for me against the mighty.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>From <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6638P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6638P\"></sup>Ephraim their root <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6638Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6638Q\"></sup>they marched down into the valley,following you, Benjamin, with your kinsmen;from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6638R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6638R\"></sup>Machir marched down the commanders,and from Zebulun those who bear the lieutenant's staff;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>the princes of Issachar came with Deborah,and Issachar faithful to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6639S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6639S\"></sup>Barak;into the valley they rushed at his heels.Among the clans of Reubenthere were great searchings of heart.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Why did you sit still <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6640T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6640T\"></sup>among the sheepfolds,to hear the whistling for the flocks?Among the clans of Reubenthere were great searchings of heart.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6641U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6641U\"></sup>Gilead stayed beyond the Jordan;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6641V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6641V\"></sup>and Dan, why did he stay with the ships?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6641W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6641W\"></sup>Asher sat still <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6641X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6641X\"></sup>at the coast of the sea,staying by his landings.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6642Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6642Y\"></sup>Zebulun is a people who risked their lives to the death;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6642Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6642Z\"></sup>Naphtali, too, on the heights of the field.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“The kings came, they fought;then fought the kings of Canaan,at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6643AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6643AA\"></sup>Taanach, by the waters of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6643AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6643AB\"></sup>Megiddo;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6643AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6643AC\"></sup>they got no spoils of silver.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6644AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6644AD\"></sup>From heaven the stars fought,from their courses they fought against Sisera.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6645AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6645AE\"></sup>The torrent Kishon swept them away,the ancient torrent, the torrent Kishon.March on, my soul, with might!",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“Then loud beat the horses' hoofswith the galloping, galloping of his steeds.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“Curse Meroz, says the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,curse its inhabitants thoroughly,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6647AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6647AF\"></sup>because they did not come to the help of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,to the help of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> against the mighty.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“Most blessed of women be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6648AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6648AG\"></sup>Jael,the wife of Heber the Kenite,of tent-dwelling women most blessed.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6649AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6649AH\"></sup>He asked for water and she gave him milk;she brought him curds in a noble's bowl.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6650AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6650AI\"></sup>She sent her hand to the tent pegand her right hand to the workmen's mallet;she struck Sisera;she crushed his head;she shattered and pierced his temple.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Between her feethe sank, he fell, he lay still;between her feethe sank, he fell;where he sank,there he fell—dead.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6652AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6652AJ\"></sup>“Out of the window she peered,the mother of Sisera wailed through <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6652AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6652AK\"></sup>the lattice:‘Why is his chariot so long in coming?Why tarry the hoofbeats of his chariots?’",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Her wisest princesses answer,indeed, she answers herself,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>‘Have they not found and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6654AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6654AL\"></sup>divided the spoil?—A womb or two for every man;spoil of dyed materials for Sisera,spoil of dyed materials embroidered,two pieces of dyed work embroidered for the neck as spoil?’",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6655AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6655AM\"></sup>“So may all your enemies perish, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>!But your friends be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6655AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6655AN\"></sup>like the sun <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6655AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6655AO\"></sup>as he rises in his might.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6655AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6655AP\"></sup>And the land had rest for forty years."
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6656A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6656A\"></sup>The people of Israel did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave them into the hand of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6656B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6656B\"></sup>Midian seven years.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And the hand of Midian overpowered Israel, and because of Midian the people of Israel made for themselves the dens that are in the mountains and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6657C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6657C\"></sup>the caves and the strongholds.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>For whenever the Israelites planted crops, the Midianites and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6658D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6658D\"></sup>the Amalekites and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6658E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6658E\"></sup>the people of the East would come up against them.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>They would encamp against them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6659F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6659F\"></sup>and devour the produce of the land, as far as Gaza, and leave no sustenance in Israel and no sheep or ox or donkey.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>For they would come up with their livestock and their tents; they would come <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6660G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6660G\"></sup>like locusts in number—both they and their camels could not be counted—so that they laid waste the land as they came in.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And Israel was brought very low because of Midian. And the people of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6661H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6661H\"></sup>cried out for help to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When the people of Israel cried out to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> on account of the Midianites,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent a prophet to the people of Israel. And he said to them, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6663I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6663I\"></sup>I led you up from Egypt and brought you out of the house of slavery.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And I delivered you from the hand of the Egyptians and from the hand of all who oppressed you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6664J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6664J\"></sup>drove them out before you and gave you their land.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And I said to you, ‘I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6665K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6665K\"></sup>you shall not fear the gods of the Amorites in whose land you dwell.’ But you have not obeyed my voice.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came and sat under the terebinth at Ophrah, which belonged to Joash <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6666L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6666L\"></sup>the Abiezrite, while his son <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6666M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6666M\"></sup>Gideon was beating out wheat in the winepress to hide it from the Midianites.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6667N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6667N\"></sup>the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared to him and said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6667O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6667O\"></sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is with you, O mighty man of valor.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And Gideon said to him, “Please, my lord, if the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is with us, why then has all this happened to us? And where are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6668P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6668P\"></sup>all his wonderful deeds <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6668Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6668Q\"></sup>that our fathers recounted to us, saying, ‘Did not the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> bring us up from Egypt?’ But now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has forsaken us and given us into the hand of Midian.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> turned to him and said, “Go in this might of yours and save Israel from the hand of Midian; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6669R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6669R\"></sup>do not I send you?”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And he said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6670S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6670S\"></sup>“Please, Lord, how can I save Israel? Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6670T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6670T\"></sup>my clan is the weakest in Manasseh, and I am the least in my father's house.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6671U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6671U\"></sup>“But I will be with you, and you shall strike the Midianites as one man.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And he said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6672V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6672V\"></sup>“If now I have found favor in your eyes, then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6672W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6672W\"></sup>show me a sign that it is you who speak with me.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Please <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6673X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6673X\"></sup>do not depart from here until I come to you and bring out my present and set it before you.” And he said, “I will stay till you return.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So Gideon went into his house <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6674Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6674Y\"></sup>and prepared a young goat and unleavened cakes from an ephah of flour. The meat he put in a basket, and the broth he put in a pot, and brought them to him under the terebinth and presented them.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And the angel of God said to him, “Take the meat and the unleavened cakes, and put them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6675Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6675Z\"></sup>on this rock, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6675AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6675AA\"></sup>pour the broth over them.” And he did so.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> reached out the tip of the staff that was in his hand and touched the meat and the unleavened cakes. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6676AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6676AB\"></sup>And fire sprang up from the rock and consumed the meat and the unleavened cakes. And the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> vanished from his sight.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then Gideon perceived that he was the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. And Gideon said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6677AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6677AC\"></sup>“Alas, O Lord <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">God</span>! For now I have seen the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> face to face.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6678AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6678AD\"></sup>“Peace be to you. Do not fear; you shall not die.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then Gideon built an altar there to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and called it, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6679AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6679AE\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> Is Peace. To this day it still stands at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6679AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6679AF\"></sup>Ophrah, which belongs to the Abiezrites.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>That night the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, “Take your father's bull, and the second bull seven years old, and pull down the altar of Baal that your father has, and cut down <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6680AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6680AG\"></sup>the Asherah that is beside it",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>and build an altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God on the top of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6681AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6681AH\"></sup>stronghold here, with stones laid in due order. Then take the second bull and offer it as a burnt offering with the wood of the Asherah that you shall cut down.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>So Gideon took ten men of his servants and did as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had told him. But because he was too afraid of his family and the men of the town to do it by day, he did it by night.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>When the men of the town rose early in the morning, behold, the altar of Baal was broken down, and the Asherah beside it was cut down, and the second bull was offered on the altar that had been built.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And they said to one another, “Who has done this thing?” And after they had searched and inquired, they said, “Gideon the son of Joash has done this thing.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then the men of the town said to Joash, “Bring out your son, that he may die, for he has broken down the altar of Baal and cut down the Asherah beside it.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>But Joash said to all who stood against him, “Will you contend for Baal? Or will you save him? Whoever contends for him shall be put to death by morning. If he is a god, let him contend for himself, because his altar has been broken down.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Therefore on that day Gideon was called <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6687AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6687AI\"></sup>Jerubbaal, that is to say, “Let Baal contend against him,” because he broke down his altar.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6688AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6688AJ\"></sup>all the Midianites and the Amalekites and the people of the East came together, and they crossed the Jordan and encamped in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6688AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6688AK\"></sup>the Valley of Jezreel.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6689AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6689AL\"></sup>the Spirit of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> clothed Gideon, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6689AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6689AM\"></sup>and he sounded the trumpet, and the Abiezrites were called out to follow him.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6690AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6690AN\"></sup>And he sent messengers throughout all Manasseh, and they too were called out to follow him. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6690AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6690AO\"></sup>And he sent messengers to Asher, Zebulun, and Naphtali, and they went up to meet them.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6691AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6691AP\"></sup>Then Gideon said to God, “If you will save Israel by my hand, as you have said,",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>behold, I am laying a fleece of wool on the threshing floor. If there is dew on the fleece alone, and it is dry on all the ground, then I shall know that you will save Israel by my hand, as you have said.”",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>And it was so. When he rose early next morning and squeezed the fleece, he wrung enough dew from the fleece to fill a bowl with water.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Then Gideon said to God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6694AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6694AQ\"></sup>“Let not your anger burn against me; let me speak just once more. Please let me test just once more with the fleece. Please let it be dry on the fleece only, and on all the ground let there be dew.”",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>And God did so that night; and it was dry on the fleece only, and on all the ground there was dew."
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6696A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6696A\"></sup>Jerubbaal (that is, Gideon) and all the people who were with him rose early and encamped beside <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6696B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6696B\"></sup>the spring of Harod. And the camp of Midian was north of them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6696C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6696C\"></sup>by the hill of Moreh, in the valley.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Gideon, “The people with you are too many for me to give the Midianites into their hand, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6697D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6697D\"></sup>lest Israel boast over me, saying, ‘My own hand has saved me.’",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Now therefore proclaim in the ears of the people, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6698E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6698E\"></sup>‘Whoever is fearful and trembling, let him return home and hurry away from Mount Gilead.’” Then 22,000 of the people returned, and 10,000 remained.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Gideon, “The people are still too many. Take them down to the water, and I will test them for you there, and anyone of whom I say to you, ‘This one shall go with you,’ shall go with you, and anyone of whom I say to you, ‘This one shall not go with you,’ shall not go.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So he brought the people down to the water. And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Gideon, “Every one who laps the water with his tongue, as a dog laps, you shall set by himself. Likewise, every one who kneels down to drink.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And the number of those who lapped, putting their hands to their mouths, was 300 men, but all the rest of the people knelt down to drink water.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Gideon, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6702F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6702F\"></sup>“With the 300 men who lapped I will save you and give the Midianites into your hand, and let all the others go every man to his home.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So the people took provisions in their hands, and their trumpets. And he sent all the rest of Israel every man to his tent, but retained the 300 men. And the camp of Midian was below him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6703G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6703G\"></sup>in the valley.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>That same <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6704H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6704H\"></sup>night the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, “Arise, go down against the camp, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6704I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6704I\"></sup>for I have given it into your hand.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But if you are afraid to go down, go down to the camp with Purah your servant.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6706J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6706J\"></sup>And you shall hear what they say, and afterward your hands shall be strengthened to go down against the camp.” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6706K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6706K\"></sup>Then he went down with Purah his servant to the outposts of the armed men who were in the camp.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And the Midianites and the Amalekites and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6707L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6707L\"></sup>all the people of the East lay along the valley like locusts in abundance, and their camels were without number, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6707M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6707M\"></sup>as the sand that is on the seashore in abundance.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>When Gideon came, behold, a man was telling a dream to his comrade. And he said, “Behold, I dreamed a dream, and behold, a cake of barley bread tumbled into the camp of Midian and came to the tent and struck it so that it fell and turned it upside down, so that the tent lay flat.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And his comrade answered, “This is no other than the sword of Gideon the son of Joash, a man of Israel; God has given into his hand Midian and all the camp.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>As soon as Gideon heard the telling of the dream and its interpretation, he worshiped. And he returned to the camp of Israel and said, “Arise, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given the host of Midian into your hand.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And he divided the 300 men into three companies and put trumpets into the hands of all of them and empty jars, with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6711N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6711N\"></sup>torches inside the jars.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And he said to them, “Look at me, and do likewise. When I come to the outskirts of the camp, do as I do.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When I blow the trumpet, I and all who are with me, then blow the trumpets also on every side of all the camp and shout, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6713O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6713O\"></sup>‘For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and for Gideon.’”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So Gideon and the hundred men who were with him came to the outskirts of the camp at the beginning of the middle watch, when they had just set the watch. And they blew the trumpets and smashed the jars that were in their hands.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then the three companies blew the trumpets and broke the jars. They held in their left hands the torches, and in their right hands the trumpets to blow. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6715P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6715P\"></sup>And they cried out, “A sword for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and for Gideon!”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Every man stood in his place around the camp, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6716Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6716Q\"></sup>and all the army ran. They cried out and fled.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6717R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6717R\"></sup>When they blew the 300 trumpets, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6717S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6717S\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> set <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6717T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6717T\"></sup>every man's sword against his comrade and against all the army. And the army fled as far as Beth-shittah toward Zererah, as far as the border of Abel-meholah, by Tabbath.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And the men of Israel were called out from Naphtali and from Asher and from all Manasseh, and they pursued after Midian.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6719U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6719U\"></sup>Gideon sent messengers throughout <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6719V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6719V\"></sup>all the hill country of Ephraim, saying, “Come down against the Midianites and capture the waters against them, as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6719W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6719W\"></sup>Beth-barah, and also the Jordan.” So all the men of Ephraim were called out, and they captured the waters as far as Beth-barah, and also the Jordan.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And they captured <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6720X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6720X\"></sup>the two princes of Midian, Oreb and Zeeb. They killed Oreb <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6720Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6720Y\"></sup>at the rock of Oreb, and Zeeb they killed at the winepress of Zeeb. Then they pursued Midian, and they brought the heads of Oreb and Zeeb to Gideon <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6720Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6720Z\"></sup>across the Jordan."
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6721A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6721A\"></sup>Then the men of Ephraim said to him, “What is this that you have done to us, not to call us when you went to fight against Midian?” And they accused him fiercely.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And he said to them, “What have I done now in comparison with you? Is not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6722B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6722B\"></sup>the gleaning of the grapes of Ephraim better than the grape harvest of Abiezer?",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6723C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6723C\"></sup>God has given into your hands the princes of Midian, Oreb and Zeeb. What have I been able to do in comparison with you?” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6723D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6723D\"></sup>Then their anger against him subsided when he said this.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And Gideon came to the Jordan and crossed over, he and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6724E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6724E\"></sup>the 300 men who were with him, exhausted yet pursuing.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So he said to the men of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6725F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6725F\"></sup>Succoth, “Please give loaves of bread to the people who follow me, for they are exhausted, and I am pursuing after Zebah and Zalmunna, the kings of Midian.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And the officials of Succoth said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6726G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6726G\"></sup>“Are the hands of Zebah and Zalmunna already in your hand, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6726H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6726H\"></sup>that we should give bread to your army?”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So Gideon said, “Well then, when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given Zebah and Zalmunna into my hand, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6727I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6727I\"></sup>I will flail your flesh with the thorns of the wilderness and with briers.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And from there he went up to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6728J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6728J\"></sup>Penuel, and spoke to them in the same way, and the men of Penuel answered him as the men of Succoth had answered.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And he said to the men of Penuel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6729K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6729K\"></sup>“When I come again in peace, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6729L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6729L\"></sup>I will break down this tower.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now Zebah and Zalmunna were in Karkor with their army, about 15,000 men, all who were left of all the army of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6730M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6730M\"></sup>the people of the East, for there had fallen 120,000 men <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6730N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6730N\"></sup>who drew the sword.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And Gideon went up by the way of the tent dwellers east of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6731O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6731O\"></sup>Nobah and Jogbehah and attacked the army, for the army felt <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6731P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6731P\"></sup>secure.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And Zebah and Zalmunna fled, and he pursued them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6732Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6732Q\"></sup>and captured the two kings of Midian, Zebah and Zalmunna, and he threw all the army into a panic.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then Gideon the son of Joash returned from the battle by the ascent of Heres.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And he captured a young man of Succoth and questioned him. And he wrote down for him the officials and elders of Succoth, seventy-seven men.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And he came to the men of Succoth and said, “Behold Zebah and Zalmunna, about whom you taunted me, saying, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6735R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6735R\"></sup>‘Are the hands of Zebah and Zalmunna already in your hand, that we should give bread to your men who are exhausted?’”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And he took the elders of the city, and he took thorns of the wilderness and briers and with them taught the men of Succoth a lesson.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6737S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6737S\"></sup>And he broke down the tower of Penuel and killed the men of the city.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then he said to Zebah and Zalmunna, “Where are the men whom you killed at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6738T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6738T\"></sup>Tabor?” They answered, “As you are, so were they. Every one of them resembled the son of a king.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And he said, “They were my brothers, the sons of my mother. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6739U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6739U\"></sup>As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, if you had saved them alive, I would not kill you.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So he said to Jether his firstborn, “Rise and kill them!” But the young man did not draw his sword, for he was afraid, because he was still a young man.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then Zebah and Zalmunna said, “Rise yourself and fall upon us, for as the man is, so is his strength.” And Gideon arose and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6741V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6741V\"></sup>killed Zebah and Zalmunna, and he took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6741W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6741W\"></sup>the crescent ornaments that were on the necks of their camels.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then the men of Israel said to Gideon, “Rule over us, you and your son and your grandson also, for you have saved us from the hand of Midian.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Gideon said to them, “I will not rule over you, and my son will not rule over you; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6743X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6743X\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will rule over you.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And Gideon said to them, “Let me make a request of you: every one of you give me the earrings from his spoil.” (For they had golden earrings, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6744Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6744Y\"></sup>because they were Ishmaelites.)",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And they answered, “We will willingly give them.” And they spread a cloak, and every man threw in it the earrings of his spoil.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And the weight of the golden earrings that he requested was 1,700 shekels of gold, besides <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6746Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6746Z\"></sup>the crescent ornaments and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6746AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6746AA\"></sup>the pendants and the purple garments worn by the kings of Midian, and besides the collars that were around the necks of their camels.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And Gideon <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6747AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6747AB\"></sup>made an ephod of it and put it in his city, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6747AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6747AC\"></sup>in Ophrah. And all Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6747AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6747AD\"></sup>whored after it there, and it became a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6747AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6747AE\"></sup>snare to Gideon and to his family.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So Midian was subdued before the people of Israel, and they raised their heads no more. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6748AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6748AF\"></sup>And the land had rest forty years in the days of Gideon.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6749AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6749AG\"></sup>Jerubbaal the son of Joash went and lived in his own house.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Now Gideon had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6750AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6750AH\"></sup>seventy sons, his own offspring, for he had many wives.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And his concubine <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6751AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6751AI\"></sup>who was in Shechem also bore him a son, and he called his name Abimelech.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And Gideon the son of Joash died <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6752AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6752AJ\"></sup>in a good old age and was buried in the tomb of Joash his father, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6752AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6752AK\"></sup>at Ophrah of the Abiezrites.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6753AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6753AL\"></sup>As soon as Gideon died, the people of Israel turned again and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6753AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6753AM\"></sup>whored after the Baals and made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6753AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6753AN\"></sup>Baal-berith their god.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>And the people of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6754AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6754AO\"></sup>did not remember the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God, who had delivered them from the hand of all their enemies on every side,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6755AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6755AP\"></sup>and they did not show steadfast love to the family of Jerubbaal (that is, Gideon) in return for all the good that he had done to Israel."
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>Now Abimelech the son of Jerubbaal went to Shechem to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6756A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6756A\"></sup>his mother's relatives and said to them and to the whole clan of his mother's family,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Say in the ears of all the leaders of Shechem, ‘Which is better for you, that all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6757B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6757B\"></sup>seventy of the sons of Jerubbaal rule over you, or that one rule over you?’ Remember also that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6757C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6757C\"></sup>I am <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6757D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6757D\"></sup>your bone and your flesh.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And his mother's relatives spoke all these words on his behalf in the ears of all the leaders of Shechem, and their hearts inclined to follow Abimelech, for they said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6758E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6758E\"></sup>“He is our brother.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And they gave him seventy pieces of silver out of the house of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6759F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6759F\"></sup>Baal-berith with which Abimelech hired <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6759G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6759G\"></sup>worthless and reckless fellows, who followed him.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And he went to his father's house at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6760H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6760H\"></sup>Ophrah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6760I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6760I\"></sup>and killed his brothers the sons of Jerubbaal, seventy men, on one stone. But Jotham the youngest son of Jerubbaal was left, for he hid himself.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And all the leaders of Shechem came together, and all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6761J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6761J\"></sup>Beth-millo, and they went and made Abimelech king, by the oak of the pillar at Shechem.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When it was told to Jotham, he went and stood on top of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6762K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6762K\"></sup>Mount Gerizim and cried aloud and said to them, “Listen to me, you leaders of Shechem, that God may listen to you.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6763L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6763L\"></sup>The trees once went out to anoint a king over them, and they said to the olive tree, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6763M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6763M\"></sup>‘Reign over us.’",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But the olive tree said to them, ‘Shall I leave my abundance, by which gods and men are honored, and go hold sway over the trees?’",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And the trees said to the fig tree, ‘You come and reign over us.’",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But the fig tree said to them, ‘Shall I leave my sweetness and my good fruit and go hold sway over the trees?’",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And the trees said to the vine, ‘You come and reign over us.’",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But the vine said to them, ‘Shall I leave my wine that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6768N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6768N\"></sup>cheers God and men and go hold sway over the trees?’",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then all the trees said to the bramble, ‘You come and reign over us.’",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And the bramble said to the trees, ‘If in good faith you are anointing me king over you, then come and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6770O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6770O\"></sup>take refuge in my shade, but if not, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6770P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6770P\"></sup>let fire come out of the bramble and devour <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6770Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6770Q\"></sup>the cedars of Lebanon.’",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“Now therefore, if you acted in good faith and integrity when you made Abimelech king, and if you have dealt well with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6771R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6771R\"></sup>Jerubbaal and his house and have done to him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6771S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6771S\"></sup>as his deeds deserved—",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>for my father fought for you and risked his life and delivered you from the hand of Midian,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and you have risen up against my father's house this day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6773T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6773T\"></sup>and have killed his sons, seventy men on one stone, and have made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6773U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6773U\"></sup>Abimelech, the son of his female servant, king over the leaders of Shechem, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6773V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6773V\"></sup>because he is your relative—",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>if you then have acted in good faith and integrity with Jerubbaal and with his house this day, then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6774W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6774W\"></sup>rejoice in Abimelech, and let him also rejoice in you.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But if not, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6775X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6775X\"></sup>let fire come out from Abimelech and devour the leaders of Shechem and Beth-millo; and let fire come out from the leaders of Shechem and from Beth-millo and devour Abimelech.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And Jotham ran away and fled and went to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6776Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6776Y\"></sup>Beer and lived there, because of Abimelech his brother.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Abimelech ruled over Israel three years.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6778Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6778Z\"></sup>And God sent an evil spirit between Abimelech and the leaders of Shechem, and the leaders of Shechem <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6778AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6778AA\"></sup>dealt treacherously with Abimelech,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6779AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6779AB\"></sup>that the violence done to the seventy sons of Jerubbaal might come, and their blood be laid on Abimelech their brother, who killed them, and on the men of Shechem, who strengthened his hands to kill his brothers.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And the leaders of Shechem put men in ambush against him on the mountaintops, and they robbed all who passed by them along that way. And it was told to Abimelech.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And Gaal the son of Ebed moved into Shechem with his relatives, and the leaders of Shechem put confidence in him.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And they went out into the field and gathered the grapes from their vineyards and trod them and held a festival; and they went into <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6782AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6782AC\"></sup>the house of their god and ate and drank and reviled Abimelech.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And Gaal the son of Ebed said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6783AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6783AD\"></sup>“Who is Abimelech, and who are we of Shechem, that we should serve him? Is he not the son of Jerubbaal, and is not Zebul his officer? Serve the men of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6783AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6783AE\"></sup>Hamor the father of Shechem; but why should we serve him?",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Would that this people were under my hand! Then I would remove Abimelech. I would say to Abimelech, ‘Increase your army, and come out.’”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>When Zebul the ruler of the city heard the words of Gaal the son of Ebed, his anger was kindled.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And he sent messengers to Abimelech secretly, saying, “Behold, Gaal the son of Ebed and his relatives have come to Shechem, and they are stirring up the city against you.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Now therefore, go by night, you and the people who are with you, and set an ambush in the field.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Then in the morning, as soon as the sun is up, rise early and rush upon the city. And when he and the people who are with him come out against you, you may do to them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6788AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6788AF\"></sup>as your hand finds to do.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>So Abimelech and all the men who were with him rose up by night and set an ambush against Shechem in four companies.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>And Gaal the son of Ebed went out and stood in the entrance of the gate of the city, and Abimelech and the people who were with him rose from the ambush.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>And when Gaal saw the people, he said to Zebul, “Look, people are coming down from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6791AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6791AG\"></sup>the mountaintops!” And Zebul said to him, “You mistake the shadow of the mountains for men.”",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Gaal spoke again and said, “Look, people are coming down from the center of the land, and one company is coming from the direction of the Diviners' Oak.”",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Then Zebul said to him, “Where is your mouth now, you who said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6793AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6793AH\"></sup>‘Who is Abimelech, that we should serve him?’ Are not these the people whom you despised? Go out now and fight with them.”",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>And Gaal went out at the head of the leaders of Shechem and fought with Abimelech.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>And Abimelech chased him, and he fled before him. And many fell wounded, up to the entrance of the gate.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>And Abimelech lived at Arumah, and Zebul drove out Gaal and his relatives, so that they could not dwell at Shechem.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>On the following day, the people went out into the field, and Abimelech was told.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>He took his people and divided them into three companies and set an ambush in the fields. And he looked and saw the people coming out of the city. So he rose against them and killed them.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Abimelech and the company that was with him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6799AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6799AI\"></sup>rushed forward and stood at the entrance of the gate of the city, while the two companies rushed upon all who were in the field and killed them.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>And Abimelech fought against the city all that day. He captured the city and killed the people who were in it, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6800AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6800AJ\"></sup>he razed the city and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6800AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6800AK\"></sup>sowed it with salt.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>When all the leaders of the Tower of Shechem heard of it, they entered <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6801AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6801AL\"></sup>the stronghold of the house of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6801AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6801AM\"></sup>El-berith.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>Abimelech was told that all the leaders of the Tower of Shechem were gathered together.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>And Abimelech went up to Mount <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6803AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6803AN\"></sup>Zalmon, he and all the people who were with him. And Abimelech took an axe in his hand and cut down a bundle of brushwood and took it up and laid it on his shoulder. And he said to the men who were with him, “What you have seen me do, hurry and do as I have done.”",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>So every one of the people cut down his bundle and following Abimelech put it against <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6804AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6804AO\"></sup>the stronghold, and they set the stronghold on fire over them, so that all the people of the Tower of Shechem also died, about 1,000 men and women.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>Then Abimelech went to Thebez and encamped against Thebez and captured it.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>But there was a strong tower within the city, and all the men and women and all the leaders of the city fled to it and shut themselves in, and they went up to the roof of the tower.",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>And Abimelech came to the tower and fought against it and drew near to the door of the tower to burn it with fire.",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6808AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6808AP\"></sup>And a certain woman threw an upper millstone on Abimelech's head and crushed his skull.",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6809AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6809AQ\"></sup>Then he called quickly to the young man his armor-bearer and said to him, “Draw your sword and kill me, lest they say of me, ‘A woman killed him.’” And his young man thrust him through, and he died.",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>And when the men of Israel saw that Abimelech was dead, everyone departed to his home.",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6811AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6811AR\"></sup>Thus God returned the evil of Abimelech, which he committed against his father in killing his seventy brothers.",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>And God also made all the evil of the men of Shechem return on their heads, and upon them came <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6812AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6812AS\"></sup>the curse of Jotham the son of Jerubbaal."
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>After Abimelech there arose to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6813A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6813A\"></sup>save Israel Tola the son of Puah, son of Dodo, a man of Issachar, and he lived at Shamir in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6813B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6813B\"></sup>the hill country of Ephraim.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And he judged Israel twenty-three years. Then he died and was buried at Shamir.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>After him arose Jair the Gileadite, who judged Israel twenty-two years.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And he had thirty sons who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6816C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6816C\"></sup>rode on thirty donkeys, and they had thirty cities, called Havvoth-jair to this day, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6816D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6816D\"></sup>which are in the land of Gilead.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And Jair died and was buried in Kamon.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6818E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6818E\"></sup>The people of Israel again did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6818F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6818F\"></sup>and served the Baals and the Ashtaroth, the gods of Syria, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6818G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6818G\"></sup>the gods of Sidon, the gods of Moab, the gods of the Ammonites, and the gods of the Philistines. And they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6818H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6818H\"></sup>forsook the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and did not serve him.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was kindled against Israel, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6819I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6819I\"></sup>he sold them into the hand of the Philistines and into the hand of the Ammonites,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and they crushed and oppressed the people of Israel that year. For eighteen years they oppressed all the people of Israel who were beyond the Jordan in the land of the Amorites, which is in Gilead.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And the Ammonites crossed the Jordan to fight also against Judah and against Benjamin and against the house of Ephraim, so that Israel was severely distressed.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And the people of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6822J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6822J\"></sup>cried out to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, saying, “We have sinned against you, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6822K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6822K\"></sup>we have forsaken our God and have served the Baals.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to the people of Israel, “Did I not save you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6823L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6823L\"></sup>from the Egyptians and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6823M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6823M\"></sup>from the Amorites, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6823N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6823N\"></sup>from the Ammonites and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6823O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6823O\"></sup>from the Philistines?",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The Sidonians also, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6824P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6824P\"></sup>the Amalekites and the Maonites oppressed you, and you cried out to me, and I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6824Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6824Q\"></sup>saved you out of their hand.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Yet you have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6825R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6825R\"></sup>forsaken me and served other gods; therefore I will save you no more.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Go and cry out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6826S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6826S\"></sup>to the gods whom you have chosen; let them save you in the time of your distress.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And the people of Israel said to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “We have sinned; do to us whatever seems good to you. Only please deliver us this day.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So they put away the foreign gods from among them and served the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6828T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6828T\"></sup>he became impatient over the misery of Israel.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then the Ammonites were called to arms, and they encamped in Gilead. And the people of Israel came together, and they encamped at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6829U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6829U\"></sup>Mizpah.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And the people, the leaders of Gilead, said one to another, “Who is the man who will begin to fight against the Ammonites? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6830V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6830V\"></sup>He shall be head over all the inhabitants of Gilead.”"
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6831A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6831A\"></sup>Jephthah the Gileadite was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6831B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6831B\"></sup>a mighty warrior, but he was the son of a prostitute. Gilead was the father of Jephthah.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And Gilead's wife also bore him sons. And when his wife's sons grew up, they drove Jephthah out and said to him, “You shall not have an inheritance in our father's house, for you are the son of another woman.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then Jephthah fled from his brothers and lived in the land of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6833C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6833C\"></sup>Tob, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6833D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6833D\"></sup>worthless fellows collected around Jephthah and went out with him.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>After a time the Ammonites made war against Israel.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And when the Ammonites made war against Israel, the elders of Gilead went to bring Jephthah from the land of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6835E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6835E\"></sup>Tob.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And they said to Jephthah, “Come and be our leader, that we may fight against the Ammonites.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But Jephthah said to the elders of Gilead, “Did you not hate me and drive me out of my father's house? Why have you come to me now when you are in distress?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And the elders of Gilead said to Jephthah, “That is why we have turned to you now, that you may go with us and fight against the Ammonites and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6838F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6838F\"></sup>be our head over all the inhabitants of Gilead.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Jephthah said to the elders of Gilead, “If you bring me home again to fight against the Ammonites, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gives them over to me, I will be your head.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And the elders of Gilead said to Jephthah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6840G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6840G\"></sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will be witness between us, if we do not do as you say.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So Jephthah went with the elders of Gilead, and the people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6841H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6841H\"></sup>made him head and leader over them. And Jephthah spoke all his words <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6841I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6841I\"></sup>before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6841J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6841J\"></sup>Mizpah.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then Jephthah sent messengers to the king of the Ammonites and said, “What do you have against me, that you have come to me to fight against my land?”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And the king of the Ammonites answered the messengers of Jephthah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6843K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6843K\"></sup>“Because Israel on coming up from Egypt took away my land, from the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6843L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6843L\"></sup>Arnon to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6843M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6843M\"></sup>Jabbok and to the Jordan; now therefore restore it peaceably.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Jephthah again sent messengers to the king of the Ammonites",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and said to him, “Thus says Jephthah: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6845N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6845N\"></sup>Israel did not take away the land of Moab or the land of the Ammonites,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>but when they came up from Egypt, Israel went through the wilderness <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6846O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6846O\"></sup>to the Red Sea and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6846P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6846P\"></sup>came to Kadesh.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6847Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6847Q\"></sup>Israel then sent messengers to the king of Edom, saying, ‘Please let us pass through your land,’ <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6847R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6847R\"></sup>but the king of Edom would not listen. And they sent also to the king of Moab, but he would not consent. So Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6847S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6847S\"></sup>remained at Kadesh.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“Then they journeyed through the wilderness and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6848T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6848T\"></sup>went around the land of Edom and the land of Moab and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6848U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6848U\"></sup>arrived on the east side of the land of Moab and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6848V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6848V\"></sup>camped on the other side of the Arnon. But they did not enter the territory of Moab, for the Arnon was the boundary of Moab.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6849W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6849W\"></sup>Israel then sent messengers to Sihon king of the Amorites, king of Heshbon, and Israel said to him, ‘Please let us pass through your land to our country,’",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>but Sihon did not trust Israel to pass through his territory, so Sihon gathered all his people together and encamped at Jahaz and fought with Israel.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, gave Sihon and all his people into the hand of Israel, and they defeated them. So Israel took possession of all the land of the Amorites, who inhabited that country.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And they took possession of all the territory of the Amorites from the Arnon to the Jabbok and from the wilderness to the Jordan.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, dispossessed the Amorites from before his people Israel; and are you to take possession of them?",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Will you not possess what <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6854X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6854X\"></sup>Chemosh your god gives you to possess? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6854Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6854Y\"></sup>And all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God has dispossessed before us, we will possess.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Now are you any better than <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6855Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6855Z\"></sup>Balak the son of Zippor, king of Moab? Did he ever contend against Israel, or did he ever go to war with them?",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>While Israel lived <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6856AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6856AA\"></sup>in Heshbon and its villages, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6856AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6856AB\"></sup>in Aroer and its villages, and in all the cities that are on the banks of the Arnon, 300 years, why did you not deliver them within that time?",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>I therefore have not sinned against you, and you do me wrong by making war on me. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6857AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6857AC\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the Judge, decide this day between the people of Israel and the people of Ammon.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>But the king of the Ammonites did not listen to the words of Jephthah that he sent to him.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6859AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6859AD\"></sup>Then the Spirit of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was upon Jephthah, and he passed through Gilead and Manasseh and passed on to Mizpah of Gilead, and from Mizpah of Gilead he passed on to the Ammonites.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And Jephthah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6860AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6860AE\"></sup>made a vow to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and said, “If you will give the Ammonites into my hand,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>then whatever comes out from the doors of my house to meet me when I return in peace from the Ammonites <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6861AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6861AF\"></sup>shall be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>'s, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6861AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6861AG\"></sup>I will offer it up for a burnt offering.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>So Jephthah crossed over to the Ammonites to fight against them, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave them into his hand.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And he struck them from Aroer to the neighborhood of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6863AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6863AH\"></sup>Minnith, twenty cities, and as far as Abel-keramim, with a great blow. So the Ammonites were subdued before the people of Israel.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Then Jephthah came to his home at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6864AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6864AI\"></sup>Mizpah. And behold, his daughter came out to meet him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6864AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6864AJ\"></sup>with tambourines and with dances. She was his only child; besides her he had neither son nor daughter.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>And as soon as he saw her, he tore his clothes and said, “Alas, my daughter! You have brought me very low, and you have become the cause of great trouble to me. For I have opened my mouth to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6865AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6865AK\"></sup>and I cannot take back my vow.”",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>And she said to him, “My father, you have opened your mouth to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; do to me according to what has gone out of your mouth, now that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has avenged you on your enemies, on the Ammonites.”",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>So she said to her father, “Let this thing be done for me: leave me alone two months, that I may go up and down on the mountains and weep for my virginity, I and my companions.”",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>So he said, “Go.” Then he sent her away for two months, and she departed, she and her companions, and wept for her virginity on the mountains.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>And at the end of two months, she returned to her father, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6869AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6869AL\"></sup>who did with her according to his vow that he had made. She had never known a man, and it became a custom in Israel",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>that the daughters of Israel went year by year to lament the daughter of Jephthah the Gileadite four days in the year."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6871A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6871A\"></sup>The men of Ephraim were called to arms, and they crossed to Zaphon and said to Jephthah, “Why did you cross over to fight against the Ammonites and did not call us to go with you? We will burn your house over you with fire.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And Jephthah said to them, “I and my people had a great dispute with the Ammonites, and when I called you, you did not save me from their hand.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And when I saw that you would not save me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6873B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6873B\"></sup>I took my life in my hand and crossed over against the Ammonites, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave them into my hand. Why then have you come up to me this day to fight against me?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then Jephthah gathered all the men of Gilead and fought with Ephraim. And the men of Gilead struck Ephraim, because they said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6874C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6874C\"></sup>“You are fugitives of Ephraim, you Gileadites, in the midst of Ephraim and Manasseh.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And the Gileadites captured <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6875D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6875D\"></sup>the fords of the Jordan against the Ephraimites. And when any of the fugitives of Ephraim said, “Let me go over,” the men of Gilead said to him, “Are you an Ephraimite?” When he said, “No,”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>they said to him, “Then say Shibboleth,” and he said, “Sibboleth,” for he could not pronounce it right. Then they seized him and slaughtered him at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6876E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6876E\"></sup>the fords of the Jordan. At that time 42,000 of the Ephraimites fell.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Jephthah judged Israel six years. Then Jephthah the Gileadite died and was buried in his city in Gilead.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>After him Ibzan of Bethlehem judged Israel.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He had thirty sons, and thirty daughters he gave in marriage outside his clan, and thirty daughters he brought in from outside for his sons. And he judged Israel seven years.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then Ibzan died and was buried at Bethlehem.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>After him Elon the Zebulunite judged Israel, and he judged Israel ten years.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then Elon the Zebulunite died and was buried at Aijalon in the land of Zebulun.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>After him Abdon the son of Hillel the Pirathonite judged Israel.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He had forty <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6884F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6884F\"></sup>sons and thirty grandsons, who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6884G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6884G\"></sup>rode on seventy donkeys, and he judged Israel eight years.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then Abdon the son of Hillel the Pirathonite died and was buried at Pirathon in the land of Ephraim, in the hill country of the Amalekites."
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>And the people of Israel again <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6886A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6886A\"></sup>did what was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, so the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6886B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6886B\"></sup>into the hand of the Philistines for forty years.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>There was a certain man of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6887C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6887C\"></sup>Zorah, of the tribe of the Danites, whose name was Manoah. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6887D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6887D\"></sup>And his wife was barren and had no children.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6888E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6888E\"></sup>And the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared to the woman and said to her, “Behold, you are barren and have not borne children, but you shall conceive and bear a son.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Therefore be careful <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6889F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6889F\"></sup>and drink no wine or strong drink, and eat nothing unclean,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>for behold, you shall conceive and bear a son. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6890G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6890G\"></sup>No razor shall come upon his head, for the child shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6890H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6890H\"></sup>a Nazirite to God from the womb, and he shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6890I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6890I\"></sup>begin to save Israel from the hand of the Philistines.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then the woman came and told her husband, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6891J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6891J\"></sup>“A man of God came to me, and his appearance was like the appearance of the angel of God, very awesome. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6891K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6891K\"></sup>I did not ask him where he was from, and he did not tell me his name,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>but he said to me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6892L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6892L\"></sup>‘Behold, you shall conceive and bear a son. So then drink no wine or strong drink, and eat nothing unclean, for the child shall be a Nazirite to God from the womb to the day of his death.’”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then Manoah prayed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and said, “O Lord, please let the man of God whom you sent come again to us and teach us what we are to do with the child who will be born.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And God listened to the voice of Manoah, and the angel of God came again to the woman as she sat in the field. But Manoah her husband was not with her.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So the woman ran quickly and told her husband, “Behold, the man who came to me the other day has appeared to me.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And Manoah arose and went after his wife and came to the man and said to him, “Are you the man who spoke to this woman?” And he said, “I am.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And Manoah said, “Now when your words come true, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6897M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6897M\"></sup>what is to be the child's manner of life, and what is his mission?”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Manoah, “Of all that I said to the woman let her be careful.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>She may not eat of anything that comes from the vine, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6899N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6899N\"></sup>neither let her drink wine or strong drink, or eat any unclean thing. All that I commanded her let her observe.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Manoah said to the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “Please let us detain you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6900O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6900O\"></sup>prepare a young goat for you.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Manoah, “If you detain me, I will not eat of your food. But if you prepare a burnt offering, then offer it to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.” (For Manoah did not know that he was the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.)",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And Manoah said to the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6902P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6902P\"></sup>“What is your name, so that, when your words come true, we may honor you?”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6903Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6903Q\"></sup>“Why do you ask my name, seeing <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6903R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6903R\"></sup>it is wonderful?”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6904S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6904S\"></sup>Manoah took the young goat with the grain offering, and offered it on the rock to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, to the one who works wonders, and Manoah and his wife were watching.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And when the flame went up toward heaven from the altar, the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> went up in the flame of the altar. Now Manoah and his wife were watching, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6905T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6905T\"></sup>and they fell on their faces to the ground.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared no more to Manoah and to his wife. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6906U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6906U\"></sup>Then Manoah knew that he was the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And Manoah said to his wife, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6907V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6907V\"></sup>“We shall surely die, for we have seen God.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But his wife said to him, “If the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had meant to kill us, he would not have accepted a burnt offering and a grain offering at our hands, or shown us all these things, or now announced to us such things as these.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And the woman bore a son and called his name Samson. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6909W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6909W\"></sup>And the young man grew, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> blessed him.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6910X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6910X\"></sup>And the Spirit of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> began to stir him in Mahaneh-dan, between <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6910Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6910Y\"></sup>Zorah and Eshtaol."
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6911A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6911A\"></sup>Samson went down to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6911B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6911B\"></sup>Timnah, and at Timnah he saw one of the daughters of the Philistines.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then he came up and told his father and mother, “I saw one of the daughters of the Philistines at Timnah. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6912C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6912C\"></sup>Now get her for me as my wife.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But his father and mother said to him, “Is there not a woman among the daughters <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6913D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6913D\"></sup>of your relatives, or among all our people, that you must go to take a wife from the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6913E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6913E\"></sup>uncircumcised Philistines?” But Samson said to his father, “Get her for me, for she is right in my eyes.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>His father and mother did not know that it was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6914F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6914F\"></sup>from the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for he was seeking an opportunity against the Philistines. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6914G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6914G\"></sup>At that time the Philistines ruled over Israel.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then Samson went down with his father and mother to Timnah, and they came to the vineyards of Timnah. And behold, a young lion came toward him roaring.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6916H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6916H\"></sup>Then the Spirit of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> rushed upon him, and although he had nothing in his hand, he tore the lion in pieces as one tears a young goat. But he did not tell his father or his mother what he had done.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then he went down and talked with the woman, and she was right in Samson's eyes.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>After some days he returned to take her. And he turned aside to see the carcass of the lion, and behold, there was a swarm of bees in the body of the lion, and honey.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He scraped it out into his hands and went on, eating as he went. And he came to his father and mother and gave some to them, and they ate. But he did not tell them that he had scraped the honey from the carcass of the lion.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>His father went down to the woman, and Samson prepared a feast there, for so the young men used to do.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>As soon as the people saw him, they brought thirty companions to be with him.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And Samson said to them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6922I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6922I\"></sup>“Let me now put a riddle to you. If you can tell me what it is, within <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6922J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6922J\"></sup>the seven days of the feast, and find it out, then I will give you thirty linen garments and thirty <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6922K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6922K\"></sup>changes of clothes,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>but if you cannot tell me what it is, then you shall give me thirty linen garments and thirty changes of clothes.” And they said to him, “Put your riddle, that we may hear it.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And he said to them,“Out of the eater came something to eat.Out of the strong came something sweet.”And in three days they could not solve the riddle.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>On the fourth day they said to Samson's wife, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6925L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6925L\"></sup>“Entice your husband to tell us what the riddle is, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6925M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6925M\"></sup>lest we burn you and your father's house with fire. Have you invited us here to impoverish us?”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And Samson's wife wept over him and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6926N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6926N\"></sup>“You only hate me; you do not love me. You have put a riddle to my people, and you have not told me what it is.” And he said to her, “Behold, I have not told my father nor my mother, and shall I tell you?”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>She wept before him the seven days that their feast lasted, and on the seventh day he told her, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6927O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6927O\"></sup>she pressed him hard. Then she told the riddle to her people.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And the men of the city said to him on the seventh day before the sun went down,“What is sweeter than honey?What is stronger than a lion?”And he said to them,“If you had not plowed with my heifer,you would not have found out my riddle.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6929P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6929P\"></sup>And the Spirit of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> rushed upon him, and he went down to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6929Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6929Q\"></sup>Ashkelon and struck down thirty men of the town and took their spoil and gave the garments to those who had told the riddle. In hot anger he went back to his father's house.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And Samson's wife was given to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6930R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6930R\"></sup>his companion, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6930S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6930S\"></sup>who had been his best man."
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span>After some days, at the time of wheat harvest, Samson went to visit his wife with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6931A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6931A\"></sup>a young goat. And he said, “I will go in to my wife in the chamber.” But her father would not allow him to go in.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And her father said, “I really thought that you utterly hated her, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6932B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6932B\"></sup>so I gave her to your companion. Is not her younger sister more beautiful than she? Please take her instead.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And Samson said to them, “This time I shall be innocent in regard to the Philistines, when I do them harm.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So Samson went and caught 300 foxes and took torches. And he turned them tail to tail and put a torch between each pair of tails.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And when he had set fire to the torches, he let the foxes go into the standing grain of the Philistines and set fire to the stacked grain and the standing grain, as well as the olive orchards.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then the Philistines said, “Who has done this?” And they said, “Samson, the son-in-law of the Timnite, because he has taken his wife <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6936C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6936C\"></sup>and given her to his companion.” And the Philistines came up and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6936D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6936D\"></sup>burned her and her father with fire.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And Samson said to them, “If this is what you do, I swear I will be avenged on you, and after that I will quit.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And he struck them hip and thigh with a great blow, and he went down and stayed in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6938E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6938E\"></sup>cleft of the rock of Etam.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then the Philistines came up and encamped in Judah and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6939F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6939F\"></sup>made a raid on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6939G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6939G\"></sup>Lehi.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And the men of Judah said, “Why have you come up against us?” They said, “We have come up to bind Samson, to do to him as he did to us.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then 3,000 men of Judah went down to the cleft of the rock of Etam, and said to Samson, “Do you not know that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6941H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6941H\"></sup>the Philistines are rulers over us? What then is this that you have done to us?” And he said to them, “As they did to me, so have I done to them.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And they said to him, “We have come down to bind you, that we may give you into the hands of the Philistines.” And Samson said to them, “Swear to me that you will not attack me yourselves.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>They said to him, “No; we will only bind you and give you into their hands. We will surely not kill you.” So they bound him with two <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6943I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6943I\"></sup>new ropes and brought him up from the rock.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When he came to Lehi, the Philistines came shouting to meet him. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6944J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6944J\"></sup>Then the Spirit of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> rushed upon him, and the ropes that were on his arms became as flax that has caught fire, and his bonds melted off his hands.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And he found a fresh jawbone of a donkey, and put out his hand and took it, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6945K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6945K\"></sup>and with it he struck 1,000 men.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And Samson said,“With the jawbone of a donkey,heaps upon heaps,with the jawbone of a donkeyhave I struck down a thousand men.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>As soon as he had finished speaking, he threw away the jawbone out of his hand. And that place <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6947L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6947L\"></sup>was called Ramath-lehi.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And he was very thirsty, and he called upon the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6948M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6948M\"></sup>“You have granted this great salvation by the hand of your servant, and shall I now die of thirst and fall into the hands of the uncircumcised?”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And God split open the hollow place that is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6949N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6949N\"></sup>at Lehi, and water came out from it. And when he drank, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6949O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6949O\"></sup>his spirit returned, and he revived. Therefore the name of it was called En-hakkore; it is at Lehi to this day.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And he judged Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6950P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6950P\"></sup>in the days of the Philistines twenty years."
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span>Samson went to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6951A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6951A\"></sup>Gaza, and there he saw a prostitute, and he went in to her.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The Gazites were told, “Samson has come here.” And they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6952B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6952B\"></sup>surrounded the place and set an ambush for him all night at the gate of the city. They kept quiet all night, saying, “Let us wait till the light of the morning; then we will kill him.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But Samson lay till midnight, and at midnight he arose and took hold of the doors of the gate of the city and the two posts, and pulled them up, bar and all, and put them on his shoulders and carried them to the top of the hill that is in front of Hebron.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>After this he loved a woman in the Valley of Sorek, whose name was Delilah.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6955C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6955C\"></sup>the lords of the Philistines came up to her and said to her, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6955D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6955D\"></sup>“Seduce him, and see where his great strength lies, and by what means we may overpower him, that we may bind him to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6955E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6955E\"></sup>humble him. And we will each give you 1,100 pieces of silver.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So Delilah said to Samson, “Please tell me where your great strength lies, and how you might be bound, that one could <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6956F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6956F\"></sup>subdue you.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Samson said to her, “If they bind me with seven fresh bowstrings that have not been dried, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6957G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6957G\"></sup>then I shall become weak and be like any other man.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then the lords of the Philistines brought up to her seven fresh bowstrings that had not been dried, and she bound him with them.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now she had men lying in ambush in an inner chamber. And she said to him, “The Philistines are upon you, Samson!” But he snapped the bowstrings, as a thread of flax snaps when it touches the fire. So the secret of his strength was not known.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then Delilah said to Samson, “Behold, you have mocked me and told me lies. Please tell me how you might be bound.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And he said to her, “If they bind me with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6961H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6961H\"></sup>new ropes that have not been used, then I shall become weak and be like any other man.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So Delilah took new ropes and bound him with them and said to him, “The Philistines are upon you, Samson!” And the men lying in ambush were in an inner chamber. But he snapped the ropes off his arms like a thread.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then Delilah said to Samson, “Until now you have mocked me and told me lies. Tell me how you might be bound.” And he said to her, “If you weave the seven locks of my head with the web and fasten it tight with the pin, then I shall become weak and be like any other man.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So while he slept, Delilah took the seven locks of his head and wove them into the web. And she made them tight with the pin and said to him, “The Philistines are upon you, Samson!” But he awoke from his sleep and pulled away the pin, the loom, and the web.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And she said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6965I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6965I\"></sup>“How can you say, ‘I love you,’ when your heart is not with me? You have mocked me these three times, and you have not told me where your great strength lies.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6966J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6966J\"></sup>when she pressed him hard with her words day after day, and urged him, his soul was vexed to death.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And he told her all his heart, and said to her, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6967K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6967K\"></sup>“A razor has never come upon my head, for I have been a Nazirite to God from my mother's womb. If my head is shaved, then my strength will leave me, and I shall become weak and be like any other man.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When Delilah saw that he had told her all his heart, she sent and called the lords of the Philistines, saying, “Come up again, for he has told me all his heart.” Then the lords of the Philistines came up to her and brought <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6968L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6968L\"></sup>the money in their hands.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>She made him sleep on her knees. And she called a man and had him shave off the seven locks of his head. Then she began <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6969M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6969M\"></sup>to torment him, and his strength left him.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And she said, “The Philistines are upon you, Samson!” And he awoke from his sleep and said, “I will go out as at other times and shake myself free.” But he did not know that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6970N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6970N\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had left him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>And the Philistines seized him and gouged out his eyes and brought him down to Gaza and bound him with bronze shackles. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6971O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6971O\"></sup>And he ground at the mill in the prison.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But the hair of his head began to grow again after it had been shaved.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Now the lords of the Philistines gathered to offer a great sacrifice to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6973P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6973P\"></sup>Dagon their god and to rejoice, and they said, “Our god has given Samson our enemy into our hand.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And when the people saw him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6974Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6974Q\"></sup>they praised their god. For they said, “Our god has given our enemy into our hand, the ravager of our country, who has killed many of us.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6975R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6975R\"></sup>when their hearts were merry, they said, “Call Samson, that he may entertain us.” So they called Samson out of the prison, and he entertained them. They made him stand between the pillars.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And Samson said to the young man who held him by the hand, “Let me feel the pillars on which the house rests, that I may lean against them.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Now the house was full of men and women. All the lords of the Philistines were there, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6977S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6977S\"></sup>on the roof there were about 3,000 men and women, who looked on while Samson entertained.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then Samson called to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and said, “O Lord <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">God</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6978T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6978T\"></sup>please remember me and please strengthen me only this once, O God, that I may be avenged on the Philistines for my two eyes.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And Samson grasped the two middle pillars on which the house rested, and he leaned his weight against them, his right hand on the one and his left hand on the other.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And Samson said, “Let me die with the Philistines.” Then he bowed with all his strength, and the house fell upon the lords and upon all the people who were in it. So the dead whom he killed at his death were more than those whom he had killed during his life.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then his brothers and all his family came down and took him and brought him up and buried him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6981U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6981U\"></sup>between Zorah and Eshtaol in the tomb of Manoah his father. He had judged Israel twenty years."
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span>There was a man of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6982A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6982A\"></sup>the hill country of Ephraim, whose name was Micah.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And he said to his mother, “The 1,100 pieces of silver that were taken from you, about which you uttered a curse, and also spoke it in my ears, behold, the silver is with me; I took it.” And his mother said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6983B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6983B\"></sup>“Blessed be my son by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And he restored the 1,100 pieces of silver to his mother. And his mother said, “I dedicate the silver to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> from my hand for my son, to make <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6984C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6984C\"></sup>a carved image and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6984D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6984D\"></sup>a metal image. Now therefore I will restore it to you.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So when he restored the money to his mother, his mother <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6985E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6985E\"></sup>took 200 pieces of silver and gave it to the silversmith, who made it into a carved image and a metal image. And it was in the house of Micah.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And the man Micah had a shrine, and he made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6986F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6986F\"></sup>an ephod and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6986G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6986G\"></sup>household gods, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6986H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6986H\"></sup>ordained one of his sons, who became his priest.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6987I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6987I\"></sup>In those days there was no king in Israel. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6987J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6987J\"></sup>Everyone did what was right in his own eyes.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now there was a young man of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6988K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6988K\"></sup>Bethlehem in Judah, of the family of Judah, who was a Levite, and he sojourned there.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And the man departed from the town of Bethlehem in Judah to sojourn where he could find a place. And as he journeyed, he came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6989L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6989L\"></sup>the hill country of Ephraim to the house of Micah.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And Micah said to him, “Where do you come from?” And he said to him, “I am a Levite of Bethlehem in Judah, and I am going to sojourn where I may find a place.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And Micah said to him, “Stay with me, and be to me <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6991M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6991M\"></sup>a father and a priest, and I will give you ten pieces of silver a year and a suit of clothes and your living.” And the Levite went in.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And the Levite <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6992N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6992N\"></sup>was content to dwell with the man, and the young man became to him like one of his sons.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And Micah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6993O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6993O\"></sup>ordained the Levite, and the young man <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6993P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6993P\"></sup>became his priest, and was in the house of Micah.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then Micah said, “Now I know that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will prosper me, because I have a Levite as priest.”"
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6995A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6995A\"></sup>In those days there was no king in Israel. And in those days <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6995B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6995B\"></sup>the tribe of the people of Dan was seeking for itself an inheritance to dwell in, for until then no inheritance among the tribes of Israel had fallen to them.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So the people of Dan sent five able men from the whole number of their tribe, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6996C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6996C\"></sup>from Zorah and from Eshtaol, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6996D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6996D\"></sup>to spy out the land and to explore it. And they said to them, “Go and explore the land.” And they came <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6996E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6996E\"></sup>to the hill country of Ephraim, to the house of Micah, and lodged there.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When they were by the house of Micah, they recognized the voice of the young Levite. And they turned aside and said to him, “Who brought you here? What are you doing in this place? What is your business here?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And he said to them, “This is how Micah dealt with me: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6998F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6998F\"></sup>he has hired me, and I have become his priest.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And they said to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-6999G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-6999G\"></sup>“Inquire of God, please, that we may know whether the journey on which we are setting out will succeed.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And the priest said to them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7000H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7000H\"></sup>“Go in peace. The journey on which you go is under the eye of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then the five men departed and came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7001I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7001I\"></sup>Laish and saw the people who were there, how they lived in security, after the manner of the Sidonians, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7001J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7001J\"></sup>quiet and unsuspecting, lacking nothing that is in the earth and possessing wealth, and how <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7001K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7001K\"></sup>they were far from the Sidonians and had no dealings with anyone.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And when they came to their brothers at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7002L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7002L\"></sup>Zorah and Eshtaol, their brothers said to them, “What do you report?”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>They said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7003M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7003M\"></sup>“Arise, and let us go up against them, for we have seen the land, and behold, it is very good. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7003N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7003N\"></sup>And will you do nothing? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7003O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7003O\"></sup>Do not be slow to go, to enter in and possess the land.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>As soon as you go, you will come to an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7004P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7004P\"></sup>unsuspecting people. The land is spacious, for God has given it into your hands, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7004Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7004Q\"></sup>a place where there is no lack of anything that is in the earth.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So 600 men of the tribe of Dan, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7005R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7005R\"></sup>armed with weapons of war, set out from Zorah and Eshtaol,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>and went up and encamped at Kiriath-jearim in Judah. On this account that place is called <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7006S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7006S\"></sup>Mahaneh-dan to this day; behold, it is west of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7006T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7006T\"></sup>Kiriath-jearim.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And they passed on from there to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7007U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7007U\"></sup>the hill country of Ephraim, and came to the house of Micah.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then the five men who had gone to scout out the country of Laish said to their brothers, “Do you know that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7008V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7008V\"></sup>in these houses there are an ephod, household gods, a carved image, and a metal image? Now therefore consider what you will do.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And they turned aside there and came to the house of the young Levite, at the home of Micah, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7009W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7009W\"></sup>asked him about his welfare.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Now the 600 men of the Danites, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7010X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7010X\"></sup>armed with their weapons of war, stood by the entrance of the gate.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7011Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7011Y\"></sup>the five men who had gone to scout out the land went up and entered and took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7011Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7011Z\"></sup>the carved image, the ephod, the household gods, and the metal image, while the priest stood by the entrance of the gate with the 600 men armed with weapons of war.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And when these went into Micah's house and took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7012AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7012AA\"></sup>the carved image, the ephod, the household gods, and the metal image, the priest said to them, “What are you doing?”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And they said to him, “Keep quiet; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7013AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7013AB\"></sup>put your hand on your mouth and come with us and be to us <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7013AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7013AC\"></sup>a father and a priest. Is it better for you to be priest to the house of one man, or to be priest to a tribe and clan in Israel?”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And the priest's heart was glad. He took the ephod and the household gods and the carved image and went along with the people.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So they turned and departed, putting the little ones and the livestock and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7015AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7015AD\"></sup>the goods in front of them.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>When they had gone a distance from the home of Micah, the men who were in the houses near Micah's house were called out, and they overtook the people of Dan.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And they shouted to the people of Dan, who turned around and said to Micah, “What is the matter with you, that you come with such a company?”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And he said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7018AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7018AE\"></sup>“You take my gods that I made and the priest, and go away, and what have I left? How then do you ask me, ‘What is the matter with you?’”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And the people of Dan said to him, “Do not let your voice be heard among us, lest angry fellows fall upon you, and you lose your life with the lives of your household.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then the people of Dan went their way. And when Micah saw that they were too strong for him, he turned and went back to his home.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>But the people of Dan took what Micah had made, and the priest who belonged to him, and they came to Laish, to a people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7021AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7021AF\"></sup>quiet and unsuspecting, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7021AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7021AG\"></sup>struck them with the edge of the sword and burned the city with fire.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And there was no deliverer because it was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7022AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7022AH\"></sup>far from Sidon, and they had no dealings with anyone. It was in the valley that belongs to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7022AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7022AI\"></sup>Beth-rehob. Then they rebuilt the city and lived in it.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And they named the city <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7023AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7023AJ\"></sup>Dan, after the name of Dan their ancestor, who was born to Israel; but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7023AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7023AK\"></sup>the name of the city was Laish at the first.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And the people of Dan set up the carved image for themselves, and Jonathan the son of Gershom, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7024AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7024AL\"></sup>son of Moses, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7024AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7024AM\"></sup>and his sons were priests to the tribe of the Danites until the day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7024AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7024AN\"></sup>of the captivity of the land.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>So they set up Micah's carved image that he made, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7025AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7025AO\"></sup>as long as the house of God was at Shiloh."
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span>In those days, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7026A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7026A\"></sup>when there was no king in Israel, a certain Levite was sojourning in the remote parts of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7026B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7026B\"></sup>the hill country of Ephraim, who took to himself a concubine from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7026C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7026C\"></sup>Bethlehem in Judah.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And his concubine was unfaithful to him, and she went away from him to her father's house at Bethlehem in Judah, and was there some four months.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then her husband arose and went after her, to speak kindly to her and bring her back. He had with him his servant and a couple of donkeys. And she brought him into her father's house. And when the girl's father saw him, he came with joy to meet him.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And his father-in-law, the girl's father, made him stay, and he remained with him three days. So they ate and drank and spent the night there.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And on the fourth day they arose early in the morning, and he prepared to go, but the girl's father said to his son-in-law, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7030D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7030D\"></sup>“Strengthen your heart with a morsel of bread, and after that you may go.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So the two of them sat and ate and drank together. And the girl's father said to the man, “Be pleased to spend the night, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7031E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7031E\"></sup>let your heart be merry.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And when the man rose up to go, his father-in-law pressed him, till he spent the night there again.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And on the fifth day he arose early in the morning to depart. And the girl's father said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7033F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7033F\"></sup>“Strengthen your heart and wait until the day declines.” So they ate, both of them.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And when the man and his concubine and his servant rose up to depart, his father-in-law, the girl's father, said to him, “Behold, now the day has waned toward evening. Please, spend the night. Behold, the day draws to its close. Lodge here and let your heart be merry, and tomorrow you shall arise early in the morning for your journey, and go home.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But the man would not spend the night. He rose up and departed and arrived opposite <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7035G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7035G\"></sup>Jebus (that is, Jerusalem). He had with him a couple of saddled donkeys, and his concubine was with him.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When they were near Jebus, the day was nearly over, and the servant said to his master, “Come now, let us turn aside to this city of the Jebusites and spend the night in it.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And his master said to him, “We will not turn aside into the city of foreigners, who do not belong to the people of Israel, but we will pass on to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7037H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7037H\"></sup>Gibeah.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And he said to his young man, “Come and let us draw near to one of these places and spend the night at Gibeah or at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7038I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7038I\"></sup>Ramah.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So they passed on and went their way. And the sun went down on them near Gibeah, which belongs to Benjamin,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and they turned aside there, to go in and spend the night at Gibeah. And he went in and sat down in the open square of the city, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7040J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7040J\"></sup>for no one took them into his house to spend the night.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And behold, an old man was coming from his work in the field at evening. The man was from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7041K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7041K\"></sup>the hill country of Ephraim, and he was sojourning in Gibeah. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7041L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7041L\"></sup>The men of the place were Benjaminites.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And he lifted up his eyes and saw the traveler in the open square of the city. And the old man said, “Where are you going? And where do you come from?”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And he said to him, “We are passing from Bethlehem in Judah to the remote parts of the hill country of Ephraim, from which I come. I went to Bethlehem in Judah, and I am going <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7043M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7043M\"></sup>to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7043N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7043N\"></sup>but no one has taken me into his house.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>We have straw and feed for our donkeys, with bread and wine for me and your female servant and the young man with your servants. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7044O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7044O\"></sup>There is no lack of anything.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And the old man said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7045P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7045P\"></sup>“Peace be to you; I will care for all your wants. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7045Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7045Q\"></sup>Only, do not spend the night in the square.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So he brought him into his house and gave the donkeys feed. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7046R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7046R\"></sup>And they washed their feet, and ate and drank.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>As they were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7047S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7047S\"></sup>making their hearts merry, behold, the men of the city, worthless fellows, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7047T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7047T\"></sup>surrounded the house, beating on the door. And they said to the old man, the master of the house, “Bring out the man who came into your house, that we may know him.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And the man, the master of the house, went out to them and said to them, “No, my brothers, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7048U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7048U\"></sup>do not act so wickedly; since this man has come into my house, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7048V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7048V\"></sup>do not do this vile thing.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7049W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7049W\"></sup>Behold, here are my virgin daughter and his concubine. Let me bring them out now. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7049X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7049X\"></sup>Violate them and do with them what seems good to you, but against this man <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7049Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7049Y\"></sup>do not do this outrageous thing.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>But the men would not listen to him. So the man seized his concubine and made her go out to them. And they knew her and abused her all night until the morning. And as the dawn began to break, they let her go.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And as morning appeared, the woman came and fell down at the door of the man's house where her master was, until it was light.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And her master rose up in the morning, and when he opened the doors of the house and went out to go on his way, behold, there was his concubine lying at the door of the house, with her hands on the threshold.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>He said to her, “Get up, let us be going.” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7053Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7053Z\"></sup>But there was no answer. Then he put her on the donkey, and the man rose up and went away to his home.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>And when he entered his house, he took a knife, and taking hold of his concubine he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7054AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7054AA\"></sup>divided her, limb by limb, into twelve pieces, and sent her throughout all the territory of Israel.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7055AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7055AB\"></sup>And all who saw it said, “Such a thing has never happened or been seen from the day that the people of Israel came up out of the land of Egypt until this day; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7055AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7055AC\"></sup>consider it, take counsel, and speak.”"
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7056A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7056A\"></sup>all the people of Israel came out, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7056B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7056B\"></sup>from Dan to Beersheba, including the land of Gilead, and the congregation assembled as one man to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7056C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7056C\"></sup>Mizpah.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7057D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7057D\"></sup>chiefs of all the people, of all the tribes of Israel, presented themselves in the assembly of the people of God, 400,000 men on foot <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7057E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7057E\"></sup>that drew the sword.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>(Now the people of Benjamin heard that the people of Israel had gone up to Mizpah.) And the people of Israel said, “Tell us, how did this evil happen?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And the Levite, the husband of the woman who was murdered, answered and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7059F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7059F\"></sup>“I came to Gibeah that belongs to Benjamin, I and my concubine, to spend the night.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7060G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7060G\"></sup>And the leaders of Gibeah rose against me and surrounded the house against me by night. They meant to kill me, and they violated my concubine, and she is dead.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7061H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7061H\"></sup>So I took hold of my concubine and cut her in pieces and sent her throughout all the country of the inheritance of Israel, for they have committed abomination and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7061I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7061I\"></sup>outrage in Israel.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Behold, you people of Israel, all of you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7062J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7062J\"></sup>give your advice and counsel here.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And all the people arose as one man, saying, “None of us will go to his tent, and none of us will return to his house.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But now this is what we will do to Gibeah: we will go up against it by lot,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and we will take ten men of a hundred throughout all the tribes of Israel, and a hundred of a thousand, and a thousand of ten thousand, to bring provisions for the people, that when they come they may repay Gibeah of Benjamin for all the outrage that they have committed in Israel.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So all the men of Israel gathered against the city, united as one man.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7067K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7067K\"></sup>And the tribes of Israel sent men through all the tribe of Benjamin, saying, “What evil is this that has taken place among you?",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now therefore give up the men, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7068L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7068L\"></sup>the worthless fellows in Gibeah, that we may put them to death <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7068M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7068M\"></sup>and purge evil from Israel.” But the Benjaminites would not listen to the voice of their brothers, the people of Israel.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then the people of Benjamin came together out of the cities to Gibeah to go out to battle against the people of Israel.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And the people of Benjamin mustered out of their cities on that day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7070N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7070N\"></sup>26,000 men <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7070O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7070O\"></sup>who drew the sword, besides the inhabitants of Gibeah, who mustered 700 chosen men.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Among all these were 700 chosen men who were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7071P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7071P\"></sup>left-handed; every one could sling a stone at a hair and not miss.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And the men of Israel, apart from Benjamin, mustered <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7072Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7072Q\"></sup>400,000 men who drew the sword; all these were men of war.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The people of Israel arose and went up to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7073R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7073R\"></sup>Bethel and inquired of God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7073S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7073S\"></sup>“Who shall go up first for us to fight against the people of Benjamin?” And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7073T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7073T\"></sup>“Judah shall go up first.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then the people of Israel rose in the morning and encamped against Gibeah.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And the men of Israel went out to fight against Benjamin, and the men of Israel drew up the battle line against them at Gibeah.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7076U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7076U\"></sup>The people of Benjamin came out of Gibeah and destroyed on that day 22,000 men of the Israelites.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But the people, the men of Israel, took courage, and again formed the battle line in the same place where they had formed it on the first day.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7078V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7078V\"></sup>And the people of Israel went up and wept before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> until the evening. And they inquired of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “Shall we again draw near to fight against our brothers, the people of Benjamin?” And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “Go up against them.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>So the people of Israel came near against the people of Benjamin the second day.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And Benjamin <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7080W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7080W\"></sup>went against them out of Gibeah the second day, and destroyed 18,000 men of the people of Israel. All these were men who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7080X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7080X\"></sup>drew the sword.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then all the people of Israel, the whole army, went up and came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7081Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7081Y\"></sup>Bethel and wept. They sat there before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and fasted that day until evening, and offered burnt offerings and peace offerings before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And the people of Israel inquired of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7082Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7082Z\"></sup>(for the ark of the covenant of God was there in those days,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7083AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7083AA\"></sup>Phinehas the son of Eleazar, son of Aaron, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7083AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7083AB\"></sup>ministered before it in those days), saying, “Shall we go out once more to battle against our brothers, the people of Benjamin, or shall we cease?” And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “Go up, for tomorrow I will give them into your hand.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7084AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7084AC\"></sup>So Israel set men in ambush around Gibeah.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And the people of Israel went up against the people of Benjamin on the third day and set themselves in array against Gibeah, as at other times.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And the people of Benjamin went out against the people and were drawn away from the city. And as at other times they began to strike and kill some of the people in the highways, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7086AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7086AD\"></sup>one of which goes up to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7086AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7086AE\"></sup>Bethel and the other to Gibeah, and in the open country, about thirty men of Israel.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And the people of Benjamin said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7087AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7087AF\"></sup>“They are routed before us, as at the first.” But the people of Israel said, “Let us flee and draw them away from the city to the highways.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>And all the men of Israel rose up out of their place and set themselves in array at Baal-tamar, and the men of Israel who were in ambush rushed out of their place from Maareh-geba.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>And there came against Gibeah 10,000 chosen men out of all Israel, and the battle was hard, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7089AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7089AG\"></sup>but the Benjaminites did not know that disaster was close upon them.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> defeated Benjamin before Israel, and the people of Israel destroyed 25,100 men of Benjamin that day. All these were men who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7090AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7090AH\"></sup>drew the sword.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>So the people of Benjamin saw that they were defeated.The men of Israel gave ground to Benjamin, because they trusted the men in ambush whom they had set against Gibeah.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7092AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7092AI\"></sup>Then the men in ambush hurried and rushed against Gibeah; the men in ambush moved out and struck all the city with the edge of the sword.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Now the appointed signal between the men of Israel and the men in the main ambush was that when they made a great cloud of smoke rise up out of the city",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>the men of Israel should turn in battle. Now Benjamin had begun to strike and kill about thirty men of Israel. They said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7094AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7094AJ\"></sup>“Surely they are defeated before us, as in the first battle.”",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>But when the signal began to rise out of the city in a column of smoke, the Benjaminites looked behind them, and behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7095AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7095AK\"></sup>the whole of the city went up in smoke to heaven.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Then the men of Israel turned, and the men of Benjamin were dismayed, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7096AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7096AL\"></sup>for they saw that disaster was close upon them.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Therefore they turned their backs before the men of Israel in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7097AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7097AM\"></sup>the direction of the wilderness, but the battle overtook them. And those who came out of the cities were destroying them in their midst.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>Surrounding the Benjaminites, they pursued them and trod them down from Nohah as far as opposite Gibeah on the east.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>Eighteen thousand men of Benjamin fell, all of them men of valor.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>And they turned <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7100AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7100AN\"></sup>and fled toward the wilderness to the rock of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7100AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7100AO\"></sup>Rimmon. Five thousand men of them were cut down in the highways. And they were pursued hard to Gidom, and 2,000 men of them were struck down.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>So all who fell that day of Benjamin were 25,000 men who drew the sword, all of them men of valor.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>But 600 men turned and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7102AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7102AP\"></sup>fled toward the wilderness to the rock of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7102AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7102AQ\"></sup>Rimmon and remained at the rock of Rimmon four months.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>And the men of Israel turned back against the people of Benjamin and struck them with the edge of the sword, the city, men and beasts and all that they found. And all the towns that they found they set on fire."
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span>Now the men of Israel had sworn <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7104A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7104A\"></sup>at Mizpah, “No one of us shall give his daughter in marriage to Benjamin.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And the people came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7105B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7105B\"></sup>Bethel and sat there till evening before God, and they lifted up their voices and wept bitterly.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And they said, “O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, why has this happened in Israel, that today there should be one tribe lacking in Israel?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And the next day the people rose early and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7107C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7107C\"></sup>built there an altar and offered burnt offerings and peace offerings.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And the people of Israel said, “Which of all the tribes of Israel did not come up in the assembly to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7108D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7108D\"></sup>For they had taken a great oath concerning him who did not come up to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to Mizpah, saying, “He shall surely be put to death.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And the people of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7109E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7109E\"></sup>had compassion for Benjamin their brother and said, “One tribe is cut off from Israel this day.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7110F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7110F\"></sup>What shall we do for wives for those who are left, since we have sworn by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that we will not give them any of our daughters for wives?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And they said, “What one is there of the tribes of Israel that did not come up to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to Mizpah?” And behold, no one had come to the camp from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7111G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7111G\"></sup>Jabesh-gilead, to the assembly.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>For when the people were mustered, behold, not one of the inhabitants of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7112H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7112H\"></sup>Jabesh-gilead was there.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So the congregation sent 12,000 of their bravest men there and commanded them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7113I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7113I\"></sup>“Go and strike the inhabitants of Jabesh-gilead with the edge of the sword; also the women and the little ones.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>This is what you shall do: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7114J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7114J\"></sup>every male and every woman that has lain with a male you shall devote to destruction.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And they found among the inhabitants of Jabesh-gilead 400 young virgins who had not known a man by lying with him, and they brought them to the camp at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7115K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7115K\"></sup>Shiloh, which is in the land of Canaan.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then the whole congregation sent word to the people of Benjamin who were at the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7116L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7116L\"></sup>rock of Rimmon and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7116M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7116M\"></sup>proclaimed peace to them.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And Benjamin returned at that time. And they gave them the women whom they had saved alive of the women of Jabesh-gilead, but they were not enough for them.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And the people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7118N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7118N\"></sup>had compassion on Benjamin because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had made a breach in the tribes of Israel.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then the elders of the congregation said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7119O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7119O\"></sup>“What shall we do for wives for those who are left, since the women are destroyed out of Benjamin?”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And they said, “There must be an inheritance for the survivors of Benjamin, that a tribe not be blotted out from Israel.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Yet we cannot give them wives from our daughters.” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7121P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7121P\"></sup>For the people of Israel had sworn, “Cursed be he who gives a wife to Benjamin.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So they said, “Behold, there is the yearly feast of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at Shiloh, which is north of Bethel, on the east of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7122Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7122Q\"></sup>the highway that goes up from Bethel to Shechem, and south of Lebonah.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And they commanded the people of Benjamin, saying, “Go and lie in ambush in the vineyards",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>and watch. If the daughters of Shiloh come out to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7124R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7124R\"></sup>dance in the dances, then come out of the vineyards and snatch each man his wife from the daughters of Shiloh, and go to the land of Benjamin.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And when their fathers or their brothers come to complain to us, we will say to them, ‘Grant them graciously to us, because we did not take for each man of them his wife in battle, neither did you give them to them, else you would now be guilty.’”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And the people of Benjamin did so and took their wives, according to their number, from the dancers whom they carried off. Then they went and returned to their inheritance <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7126S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7126S\"></sup>and rebuilt the towns and lived in them.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And the people of Israel departed from there at that time, every man to his tribe and family, and they went out from there every man to his inheritance.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-7128T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-7128T\"></sup>In those days there was no king in Israel. Everyone did what was right in his own eyes."
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;